body:
&quot;Its not my job to gank losing lanes&quot;

&quot;You should be able to handle your own lane&quot;

Now, on my real accounts, this isn&#039;t much of an issue as I rarely need help in lane.

However, last game there was Cho mid and an enemy Syndra. Syndra was getting fed early and I could tell that the Cho wasn&#039;t bad, he was just having a hard time.

Now the Jungler says its his job to get other lanes fed, to gank winning lanes.

Okay lets roll with that. Basically you are saying &quot;I am totally okay to let their mid get fed and hopefully whichever lane I help will be stronger than whatever happens over there at mid, and of course, run the high risk of losing first turret blood as well&quot;

This is fucking stupid. Shut down the fed champions, get the gold, and prevent a super snowballing champion from carrying the game. If the lane is  fucked that early its unlikely you are going to somehow counter it by getting another lane some kills. 

This idea that flat out a junlgers role does not include helping losing lanes is shortsighted.
